item.title: I baked a computer (and it worked!)
item.description: {% raw %} This weekend a friend asked me to have a look at his HP DV9500 laptop.  It was having trouble - when you turned it on, the screen showed nothing but a solid grey with a few thin black bars.  The grey increased in intensity as the system ran, until it ran off the colors that the display knew how to show. Clearly, there was a problem with the video card.
